Uh, but I was on a porch chair.

522
00:56:26,416 --> 00:56:28,748
S<i>o, you know--</i>
Don't you
even have a room?

523
00:56:28,818 --> 00:56:33,016
Uh, yes, I will at 9: 19.
Room 4 16.

524
00:56:34,491 --> 00:56:37,585
I mean, w-would you like
to go to breakfast?

525
00:56:37,660 --> 00:56:39,594
At 6:00 a.m.?

526
00:56:39,662 --> 00:56:41,789
Oh. Well, later ?

527
00:56:41,865 --> 00:56:45,198
I don't eat breakfast
on performance days.
Oh, no. Of course not.

528
00:56:45,268 --> 00:56:47,463
Um, lunch?
Mr. Collier !

529
00:56:47,537 --> 00:56:49,869
No, no, no.
It's not Mr. Collier.
Isn't that your name?

530
00:56:49,939 --> 00:56:51,873
Yes, that's
my name, but--
Shh ! Shh !

531
00:56:51,941 --> 00:56:54,000
What?
Marie. She's sleeping
in the other room.

532
00:56:54,077 --> 00:56:56,477
Marie?
My maid.

533
00:56:56,546 --> 00:56:58,446
Ooh. I'm sorry.

534
00:56:58,515 --> 00:57:01,450
[ Whispering ]
Well, of course my name
is Mr. Collier.

535
00:57:01,518 --> 00:57:05,079
But I was hoping
you'd call me
by my first name, Richard.

536
00:57:05,155 --> 00:57:07,214
Why should I ?
I don't know.

537
