Why? Is it funny?

643
01:05:10,973 --> 01:05:12,907
In a way.

644
01:05:13,976 --> 01:05:16,274
William told me
you were coming.

645
01:05:16,345 --> 01:05:18,404
Robinson?
Yes.

646
01:05:21,150 --> 01:05:23,744
He knows, somehow.

647
01:05:23,819 --> 01:05:25,753
He really does.

648
01:05:26,989 --> 01:05:29,822
He knew a lot of things
before they happened:

649
01:05:29,926 --> 01:05:31,826
my career, my--

650
01:05:37,400 --> 01:05:40,233
He told me that...

651
01:05:40,303 --> 01:05:43,238
one day I would
meet a man who'd...

652
01:05:44,807 --> 01:05:47,105
change my life.

653
01:05:47,176 --> 01:05:51,112
Did he tell you
that man would be someone
to be afraid of?

654
01:05:52,181 --> 01:05:54,445
Yes.

655
01:05:54,517 --> 01:05:57,418
And what
do you think now?

656
01:05:57,486 --> 01:05:59,954
Do you--
Do you believe that?

657
01:06:01,757 --> 01:06:03,691
No.

658
01:06:03,759 --> 01:06:06,387
You're obviously not.

659
01:06:09,632 --> 01:06:12,567
<i>[ Humming ]</i>

660
01:06:19,175 --> 01:06:21,109
That's
beautiful.
Hmm?

661
01:06:22,278 --> 01:06:24,872
What is it?

662
01:06:24,981 --> 01:06:28,246
That's Rachmaninoff,
from the Rhapsody.

663
01:06:28,317 --> 01:06:32,014
Hmm. I saw him with
the philharmonic once.

