01:06:32,054 --> 01:06:35,080
I love his music,
but I've never heard
this piece.

665
01:06:35,157 --> 01:06:38,422
Really?
Well, I'll introduce you
to it sometime.

666
01:06:58,614 --> 01:07:01,549
[ Richard ]
Sorry we had the carriage
so long. Thank you.

667
01:07:03,552 --> 01:07:05,486
See that guy's face?
[ Laughs ]

668
01:07:05,554 --> 01:07:08,489
They're gonna hang us
for horse-napping.
[ Both Laughing ]

669
01:07:12,661 --> 01:07:15,095
[ Sighs ]

670
01:07:15,164 --> 01:07:17,257
Stick out
your tongue.

671
01:07:17,333 --> 01:07:19,267
Huh?
Stick out
your tongue.

672
01:07:21,337 --> 01:07:23,737
Why? Oh, no.

673
01:07:34,650 --> 01:07:37,710
The most peculiar moment
in my life, Mr. Collier.

674
01:07:37,787 --> 01:07:40,722
I think you'll survive it,
Miss McKenna.

675
01:07:43,492 --> 01:07:45,426
What time
is it now?

676
01:07:47,596 --> 01:07:49,996
Um,

677
01:07:50,099 --> 01:07:51,999
4:30.

678
01:07:52,101 --> 01:07:54,899
Well, I must be
getting back.
You have to?

679
01:07:54,970 --> 01:07:58,235
Can't you stay
a little longer ?
No, I have to rest awhile.

680
01:07:58,307 --> 01:08:00,707
The play.
The play.
[ Laughs ]

681
01:08:02,278 --> 01:08:04,212
It's lovely.

682
01:08:06,615 --> 01:08:08,549
Where did you get it?

683
01:08:10,820 --> 01:08:12,754
It-It was given to me.

684
01:08:19,495 --> 01:08:21,429
Well, shall we?

685
01:08:25,267 --> 01:08:27,792
So... when's
the company leave?

686
01:08:29,872 --> 01:08:31,806
Tonight.

687
01:08:35,911 --> 01:08:37,845
Where are you going?

688
01:08:37,913 --> 01:08:39,847
Denver.
Oh.

689
01:08:46,222 --> 01:08:49,157
Well--
Well, thank you for
a most pleasant afternoon.

690
01:08:51,694 --> 01:08:53,855
Could we talk
just a little longer ?

691
01:08:53,929 --> 01:08:56,864
I really should
rest awhile. I--
Please.

692
01:09:02,138 --> 01:09:05,039
Very well, then.
Just for a moment or so.

693
01:09:28,998 --> 01:09:31,933
What did you want
to talk about?

694
01:09:48,350 --> 01:09:50,284
No.

695
01:10:14,076 --> 01:10:16,010
Oh, my God.

696
01:10:17,079 --> 01:10:19,013
What's happening?

697
01:10:36,131 --> 01:10:38,827
[ Knocking At Door ]

698
01:10:38,901 --> 01:10:40,835
<i>[ Robinson ]</i>
<i>McKenna?</i>

699
01:10:43,272 --> 01:10:45,433
[ Knocking ]
<i>McKenna?</i>

700
01:10:46,842 --> 01:10:48,776
Come in.

701
01:10:52,548 --> 01:10:56,484
I think you'd better go.
Have you been waiting
all this time for our return?

702
01:10:56,552 --> 01:10:58,747
This is
hardly the time--
Have you?

703
01:10:58,821 --> 01:11:00,755
Yes. Does that
surprise you?

704
01:11:00,823 --> 01:11:03,018
Our relationship
is strictly business.
S<i>trictly</i> business?

705
01:11:03,092 --> 01:11:06,550
I'm involved with you
as an actress, Mr. Robinson,
not a doormat.

706
01:11:06,629 --> 01:11:09,564
Do not attempt
to wipe your boots on me.

707
01:11:13,002 --> 01:11:15,197
Richard.

708
01:11:17,673 --> 01:11:21,074
I shall leave a ticket for you
at the theater door.

709
01:11:30,119 --> 01:11:32,178
""Excess within control,""
McKenna?

710
01:11:34,723 --> 01:11:37,590
<i>au revoir</i>.

711
01:11:37,660 --> 01:11:39,594
<i>[ Door</i> S<i>lams ]</i>

712
01:11:46,435 --> 01:11:48,198
[ Crowd Murmuring ]

713
01:11:48,304 --> 01:11:51,205
[ Waltz ]

714
01:12:07,823 --> 01:12:10,758
<i>[ applause ]</i>

715
01:12:17,166 --> 01:12:19,100
<i>[ applause</i> S<i>tops ]</i>

716
01:12:19,168 --> 01:12:22,103
Good evening, miss.
Not good at all.

717
01:12:23,172 --> 01:12:25,936
Particularly bad.

718
01:12:26,008 --> 01:12:29,409
I'll not go
downstairs again.
Oh, what is it, miss?

719
01:12:29,478 --> 01:12:31,412
[ Sighs ]
I've just been dining...

720
01:12:31,480 --> 01:12:34,415
with the man my father
is determined that I wed.

721
01:12:34,483 --> 01:12:39,216
Ooh, banker Harwell.
Banker Harwell--
yes, all 67 years...

722
01:12:39,288 --> 01:12:42,587
and five-foot-four of height
and several hundred pounds
of him !

723
01:12:42,658 --> 01:12:45,923
[ Laughter ]
He does have money,
though, miss.

724
01:12:45,994 --> 01:12:48,929
And never lets
a soul forget it.

725
01:12:48,997 --> 01:12:51,932
I'm amazed he has
the least desire
to marry.

726
01:12:52,000 --> 01:12:55,367
- He's so happily wedded
to his gold.
<i>- [ Laughter ]</i>

727
01:12:55,437 --> 01:12:57,769
<i>[ Maid ]</i>
<i>He won't be</i>
<i>that bad, miss</i>.

728
01:12:57,840 --> 01:13:01,071
There must be something
you like about 'im.

729
01:13:01,143 --> 01:13:03,703
Yes, his absence.

730
01:13:10,152 --> 01:13:13,610
The man of my dreams
has almost faded now.

731
01:13:21,430 --> 01:13:24,331
And what man
is that, miss?

732
01:13:24,433 --> 01:13:27,960
The one I have created
in my mind.

733
01:13:31,473 --> 01:13:33,407
The sort of man...

734
01:13:33,475 --> 01:13:36,603
each woman dreams of
in the deepest...

735
01:13:36,678 --> 01:13:39,613
and most secret reaches
of her heart.

736
01:13:44,086 --> 01:13:47,021
I can almost
see him now before me.

737
01:13:50,225 --> 01:13:52,693
What would I say to him...

738
01:13:54,363 --> 01:13:56,524
if he were really here?

739
01:13:57,900 --> 01:13:59,834
"<i>Forgive me</i>. "

740
01:14:01,437 --> 01:14:03,462
I've never known
this feeling.

741
01:14:05,941 --> 01:14:08,876
I've lived without it
all my life.

742
01:14:10,746 --> 01:14:13,681
Is it any wonder, then,
I failed to recognize you?

743
01:14:15,017 --> 01:14:17,042
<i>y ou've</i>...

744
01:14:17,119 --> 01:14:20,054
<i>brought it to me</i>
<i>for the first time</i>.

745
01:14:20,122 --> 01:14:22,352
Is there any way that--

746
01:14:23,959 --> 01:14:26,894
that I can tell you
how my life has changed?

747
01:14:28,330 --> 01:14:30,321
Any way at all
to let you know...

748
01:14:30,399 --> 01:14:33,197
<i>what sweetness</i>
<i>you have given me?</i>

749
01:14:34,336 --> 01:14:36,804
There is
so much to say, I--

750
01:14:40,108 --> 01:14:42,599
I cannot find the words,

751
01:14:42,678 --> 01:14:44,805
<i>except for these.:</i>

752
01:14:47,883 --> 01:14:49,817
I love you.

753
01:14:54,957 --> 01:14:57,653
And such
would I say to him,

754
01:14:57,726 --> 01:14:59,751
if he were really here.

755
01:14:59,828 --> 01:15:03,093
<i>[ applause ]</i>

756
01:15:13,642 --> 01:15:16,577
[ Applause, Cheering ]

757
01:15:37,533 --> 01:15:39,433
[ Applause Continues ]

758
01:15:39,535 --> 01:15:42,333
What, in God's name,
were you doing?
[ Murmuring ]

759
01:15:42,404 --> 01:15:45,635
Nothing.
Nothing? Rewriting
the entire first scene?

760
01:15:45,707 --> 01:15:47,971
I got it back
on course.
Elise, hold a moment.

761
01:15:48,010 --> 01:15:50,570
We've just got to take
that photograph.
Oh !

762
01:15:50,646 --> 01:15:55,481
Very well. Just a moment,
I have to change.
Quickly !

763
01:16:01,924 --> 01:16:04,188
A-And
a little flourish.

764
01:16:04,259 --> 01:16:06,193
Yes, yes.
Yes, very pretty.

765
01:16:06,261 --> 01:16:08,354
Very pretty.
Just one moment.
Here we go.

766
01:16:08,430 --> 01:16:10,921
I'm just going to focus
on that lovely--

767
01:16:10,999 --> 01:16:14,332
Oh, yes, yes, yes !
I'm just going to
put in the plate.

768
01:16:14,403 --> 01:16:16,871
One moment.
There we go.

769
01:16:18,307 --> 01:16:20,707
A little smile, please.

770
01:16:20,776 --> 01:16:24,439
Uh, not-not quite.
Uh, perhaps if you think of
something happy or bright.

771
01:16:25,647 --> 01:16:28,207
<i>y es, that's it</i>.
<i>That's it. Hold it</i>.

772
01:16:29,484 --> 01:16:31,816
<i>[</i> S<i>hutter Clicks ]</i>

773
01:16:31,887 --> 01:16:34,412
<i>Perfeect</i> !
<i>absolutely perfeect</i>.

774
01:16:52,774 --> 01:16:55,436
<i>[ actor ]</i>
<i>l say l shall have her</i> !
[ Laughter ]

775
01:16:55,510 --> 01:16:57,910
<i>[ actress ]</i>
<i>Not in my life,</i>
<i>you shall not</i>.

776
01:16:57,980 --> 01:17:01,381
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Mr. Collier ?</i>
<i>l am the one who loves her</i> !

777
01:17:01,450 --> 01:17:03,213
For you.

778
01:17:03,285 --> 01:17:05,219
<i>[ actress ]</i>
<i>Neither do you</i>.

779
01:17:05,287 --> 01:17:08,222
<i>[ actor #1 ]</i>
<i>l can provide her</i>
<i>with life's enrichments,</i>

780
01:17:08,290 --> 01:17:10,554
<i>rather than</i>
<i>the riches of life</i>.

781
01:17:10,659 --> 01:17:12,559
<i>[ Laughter ]</i>

782
01:17:12,661 --> 01:17:14,561
<i>[ actor #2 ]</i>
<i>are you sure?</i>

783
01:17:14,663 --> 01:17:17,223
<i>[ actor #1 ]</i>
<i>an old song says it best</i>.

784
01:17:17,532 --> 01:17:20,228
<i>[ Laughter, applause ]</i>

785
01:17:24,873 --> 01:17:27,808
Do you have any notion
how many years...

786
01:17:27,876 --> 01:17:30,276
I have been
with Miss McKenna?

787
01:17:32,147 --> 01:17:34,411
Since March of 1903.

788
01:17:39,488 --> 01:17:42,423
<i>March, 190</i>3.

789
01:17:42,491 --> 01:17:44,425
<i>That's correct</i>.

790
01:17:44,493 --> 01:17:46,961
S<i>he was 16</i>
<i>at the time</i>.

791
01:17:48,563 --> 01:17:51,999
<i>There she was</i>
<i>on that dingy stage</i>...

792
01:17:53,035 --> 01:17:55,629
in that <i>pathetic</i> play.

793
01:17:55,737 --> 01:17:58,365
<i>Total radiance</i>.

794
01:18:00,008 --> 01:18:03,000
It only took seconds
for me to realize...

795
01:18:03,045 --> 01:18:05,013
exactly what
she had to be.

796
01:18:06,114 --> 01:18:08,548
<i>Mrs</i>. Robinson?

797
01:18:08,617 --> 01:18:11,211
Do you actually believe...

798
01:18:11,286 --> 01:18:13,754
that I have nurtured her,

799
01:18:13,822 --> 01:18:16,552
cared for her,
molded, taught,

800
01:18:16,625 --> 01:18:19,093
developed her
for all these years,

801
01:18:19,161 --> 01:18:21,652
merely to groom
a wife?

802
01:18:21,763 --> 01:18:23,697
What, then?

803
01:18:24,800 --> 01:18:26,927
A star.

804
01:18:29,004 --> 01:18:30,972
<i>Only someone with</i>...

805
01:18:31,006 --> 01:18:33,065
the limited awareness
of your age...

806
01:18:33,141 --> 01:18:36,269
could possibly conceive
that my entire passion
for this woman...

807
01:18:36,344 --> 01:18:38,812
is no more than physical !

808
01:18:38,880 --> 01:18:41,144
<i>are you incapable</i>
<i>of understanding that</i>...

809
01:18:41,216 --> 01:18:44,652
she has it within herself
to be one of the greatest,

810
01:18:44,753 --> 01:18:46,812
if not <i>the</i> greatest...

811
01:18:46,888 --> 01:18:48,822
actress
of her generation?

812
01:18:57,399 --> 01:18:59,993
I owe you an apology.

813
01:19:00,035 --> 01:19:02,367
What?

814
01:19:02,437 --> 01:19:04,997
I understand you now.

815
01:19:05,073 --> 01:19:08,042
You have nothing but the best
motives in mind for her.

816
01:19:08,110 --> 01:19:10,271
- And you--
- But so do I.

817
01:19:10,345 --> 01:19:12,836
<i>Of course,</i>
<i>she'll continue to act,</i>

818
01:19:12,914 --> 01:19:15,041
she will continue to grow...

819
01:19:15,117 --> 01:19:18,678
and she will become
everything you want her to be.

820
01:19:18,787 --> 01:19:22,314
With you at her side?
<i>y es</i>.

821
01:19:22,390 --> 01:19:24,381
With me at her side.

822
01:19:24,459 --> 01:19:26,620
Never.

823
01:19:26,695 --> 01:19:28,925
My God.

824
01:19:28,997 --> 01:19:32,660
You really think
you own her, don't you?

825
01:19:32,768 --> 01:19:35,396
Collier, I know
who you are.

826
01:19:38,473 --> 01:19:40,532
Ever since
you came here,

827
01:19:40,609 --> 01:19:42,577
I've known
from the start.

828
01:19:43,645 --> 01:19:45,579
You came
to destroy her.

829
01:19:45,647 --> 01:19:48,081
God, you're
out of your mind.

830
01:19:48,150 --> 01:19:51,950
<i>[ Orchestra ]</i>
<i>[ applause ]</i>

831
01:19:51,987 --> 01:19:53,955
[ Grunts ]

832
01:19:53,989 --> 01:19:57,516
<i>[ Orchestra Finishes ]</i>

833
01:19:57,592 --> 01:20:00,993
<i>[ applause Continues ]</i>

834
01:20:01,029 --> 01:20:02,997
No more.
No more?

835
01:20:03,031 --> 01:20:05,226
One curtain call ?
The audience
will be furious.

836
01:20:05,300 --> 01:20:07,791
Marie, did you
find him?

837
01:20:07,869 --> 01:20:09,803
No, Miss McKenna.
Did you try his room?

838
01:20:09,871 --> 01:20:11,805
He wasn't there.
Oh !

839
01:20:13,875 --> 01:20:16,810
What did they say
at the desk?
They have not seen him.

840
01:20:16,878 --> 01:20:19,676
He left no message?
No, I'm sorry.

841
01:20:19,748 --> 01:20:22,945
[ Sighs ]
This makes
no sense at all.

842
01:20:23,018 --> 01:20:25,418
What could have happened
to him?

843
01:20:26,988 --> 01:20:28,922
Marie !

844
01:20:28,990 --> 01:20:31,925
Marie, help me
change. Quickly.

845
01:20:33,528 --> 01:20:36,053
<i>[ Knocking at Door ]</i>
Wait, Marie.

846
01:20:43,605 --> 01:20:45,539
Thank you, Marie.

847
01:20:58,587 --> 01:21:01,021
Your performance
in act one, I--

848
01:21:01,089 --> 01:21:04,217
I must say,
was somewhat eccentric.

849
01:21:04,292 --> 01:21:06,920
Where is he?
What have you done to him?

850
01:21:06,995 --> 01:21:09,486
I've done nothing, McKenna.

851
01:21:09,564 --> 01:21:11,498
Mr. Collier has left.

852
01:21:11,566 --> 01:21:14,694
<i>That's all</i>.
What do you mean?

853
01:21:14,769 --> 01:21:18,466
G<i>one</i>... <i>from the hotel</i>...

854
01:21:18,540 --> 01:21:20,474
and your life.

855
01:21:20,542 --> 01:21:22,772
I don't believe you.

856
01:21:25,013 --> 01:21:27,277
I must admit,

857
01:21:27,349 --> 01:21:29,283
he was somewhat
more charming...

858
01:21:29,351 --> 01:21:32,286
than others that
we've encountered in the past,

859
01:21:32,354 --> 01:21:34,288
<i>you and l</i>.

860
01:21:35,390 --> 01:21:37,654
<i>a trifle more sincere,</i>
<i>perhaps</i>. S<i>till--</i>

861
01:21:37,726 --> 01:21:41,218
Then he was not
the one you spoke of?

862
01:21:41,296 --> 01:21:44,959
No.
<i>Then you were wrong</i>
<i>about him, weren't you?</i>

863
01:21:46,001 --> 01:21:47,969
You were wrong.

864
01:21:50,805 --> 01:21:53,399
I love him,

865
01:21:53,475 --> 01:21:57,275
and he's going
to make me very happy.

866
01:21:57,345 --> 01:21:59,404
<i>Do you understand?</i>

867
01:22:01,616 --> 01:22:04,346
I love him.

868
01:22:04,419 --> 01:22:09,516
What difference...
can that make now?
He's gone.

869
01:22:09,591 --> 01:22:11,684
I'll find him, William.

870
01:22:13,929 --> 01:22:16,830
Don't you dare
try to stop me.

871
01:22:20,802 --> 01:22:23,737
Now, if you will excuse me
while I change.

872
01:22:25,974 --> 01:22:27,874
Of course.

873
01:22:46,962 --> 01:22:49,590
May I remind you...

874
01:22:49,664 --> 01:22:52,098
that we leave
within the hour ?

875
01:22:52,167 --> 01:22:55,398
<i>[ Door Opens,</i>
<i>Footsteps Recede ]</i>

876
01:22:55,470 --> 01:22:57,404
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

877
01:23:42,984 --> 01:23:44,918
Thank you.

878
01:23:54,429 --> 01:23:56,363
<i>[ Horse</i> S<i>norts ]</i>
[ Grunts ]

879
01:24:03,505 --> 01:24:05,439
[ Moans ]

880
01:24:10,345 --> 01:24:12,609
<i>[ Horse</i> S<i>norts ]</i>

881
01:24:12,680 --> 01:24:14,773
[ Grunting ]

882
01:24:16,851 --> 01:24:19,786
[ Grunting, Panting ]

883
01:24:33,134 --> 01:24:35,068
[ Glass Shatters ]

884
01:24:36,538 --> 01:24:38,472
[ Grunting ]

885
01:24:42,210 --> 01:24:44,144
[ Grunts ]

886
01:24:45,480 --> 01:24:47,414
Yah !

887
01:24:52,554 --> 01:24:54,488
Elise !

888
01:24:54,556 --> 01:24:56,490
Elise?

889
01:24:56,558 --> 01:24:58,492
Elise?

890
01:25:00,495 --> 01:25:04,397
[ Sighs ]
S<i>ir ?</i>

891
01:25:04,466 --> 01:25:06,400
<i>are you all right?</i>

892
01:25:06,468 --> 01:25:08,993
The company--
Are they gone?
Company?

893
01:25:09,104 --> 01:25:11,766
The ones who did
the play last night.
Are they gone?

894
01:25:11,840 --> 01:25:14,775
They left as soon
as they were packed, sir.

895
01:25:19,280 --> 01:25:22,215
Oh, come along, Arthur.
We'll be late.

896
01:26:34,122 --> 01:26:36,056
Richard !

897
01:26:50,371 --> 01:26:53,306
[ Laughing ]

898
01:27:04,485 --> 01:27:06,646
You all right?
Yes.

899
01:27:06,721 --> 01:27:08,882
I thought
I lost you.
Oh, never.

900
01:27:08,957 --> 01:27:10,891
Never, never, never !

901
01:29:00,868 --> 01:29:02,802
Mm-mmm.

902
01:29:02,870 --> 01:29:05,202
You will marry me,
won't you?

903
01:29:05,273 --> 01:29:07,207
[ Splutters ]

904
01:29:07,275 --> 01:29:09,573
[ Laughing ]
Sorry.
